author: wtopstaff
title: Dolphins-Titans Capsule
text:
By The Associated Press  41 pm 
MIAMI (1-3) at TENNESSEE (1-3) 
Sunday, 1 p.m. ET, CBS 
OPENING LINE — Titans by 1 ½ 
RECORD VS. SPREAD — Dolphins 1-3, Titans 2-1-1 
SERIES RECORD — Dolphins lead 18-16 
LAST MEETING — Titans beat Dolphins 37-3, Nov. 11, 2012 
LAST WEEK — Dolphins had bye, lost to Jets 27-14 on Oct. 4; Titans lost 14-13 to Bills 
AP PRO32 RANKING — Dolphins No. 30, Titans No. 25 
DOLPHINS OFFENSE — OVERALL (28), RUSH (31), PASS (14). 
DOLPHINS DEFENSE — OVERALL (29), RUSH (32), PASS (14). 
TITANS OFFENSE — OVERALL (16), RUSH (14), PASS (22). 
TITANS DEFENSE — OVERALL (3), RUSH (23), PASS (1). 
STREAKS, STATS AND NOTES — Dolphins interim head coach Dan Campbell makes coaching debut vs. Titans. … Dolphins have won eight of last 12 vs. Titans. … Dolphins have yet to score rushing TD this season, one of two NFL teams (Jaguars) without one. … Dolphins’ longest run this season is 17 yards. … Dolphins QB Ryan Tannehill ranks seventh with 1,080 yards passing. Tannehill has thrown two TD passes in past three games. … Dolphins WR Rishard Matthews has 100 yards or more receiving in two of past three games. … Titans QB Marcus Mariota has two or more TD passes in three of four career starts. … Mariota leads NFL rookies with eight TD passes and 99.7 passer rating. His passer rating ranks 10th in NFL. … Titans are tied with Washington for best time of possession in NFL, averaging 34:18 per game. … Titans LB Derrick Morgan has 4 ½ sacks this season. DT Jurrell Casey has 3 ½ sacks. … Fantasy Tip: Mariota finally has started using his legs as well as his arm. He is coming off career-best 47 yards rushing and has not scored in only one game this season.
